Backing up the idea:


new
-> We are building the identity and permissions layer for AI agents that need to act in the real world.
-> We let AI agents automate real-world tasks without giving them direct access to human accounts or raw API keys.
-> We initialize an identity layer, give OpenClaw a unique token, and now OpenClaw can safely automate email, phone, and calendar actions through our permissioned API.



old
-> What makes it special:
The agent has a real digital identity: email, phone, calendar, permissions, logs.
What the big vision is:
“Today we use this for customer discovery. Tomorrow this becomes the identity layer for any AI agent acting in the real world.”

-> We were building the agent identity but then thought how are we going to find customers 